VI. If a man ſteale a beaſt, and it be found in his hand, he ſhall make reſtitution two for one, if it be killed and ſold,
                        Ex. 22.1.4. reſtitution to be made of five oxen for one, of four ſheepe, goats or ſwine, for one;
                        Ex. 22.3. if the thief be not able to make reſtitution, then he to be ſold by the magiſtrates for a ſervant, till by his labour he may make due reſtitution.
